[4] Netherlands: details
Date: Tue 19 Jul 2022
Source: NL Times [abridged, edited]
https://nltimes.nl/2022/07/19/dutch-monkeypox-total-climbs-656-including-three-female-patients


The number of people in the Netherlands diagnosed with the monkeypox virus rose to 656. Since the last update on Thursday [14 Jul 2022], the National Institute for Public Health and the Environment (RIVM) registered 107 positive tests. The institute confirmed 153 infections since last week Monday [11 Jul 2022], which corresponds with the growth rate in the weeks before. The number of women who tested positive increased from one to 3. Previously, a "child of primary school age" got the virus. Most of the monkeypox cases in the Netherlands concern men who have sex with men (MSM).

